I haven't seen any discussion on this, so not sure if my proposed fix is the way to go or not. But to show you guys what I've done, and maybe help anyone else who stumbles on this issue, I use this subclass of `S3Boto3Storage` in my code by pointing `STATICFILES_STORAGE` to the subclass. Here's the code for the subclass:

```
class S3Boto3Storage(s3boto3.S3Boto3Storage):
    def listdir(self, name):
        """Instead of treating S3 as a hierarchical file system (which it is not and folders are only an illusion), this
        overridden listdir treats it as a simple list of files with no folders, only prefixes."""
        name = self._normalize_name(self._clean_name(name))
        if name and not name.endswith('/'):
            name += '/'

        return [], list(item.key for item in self.bucket.objects.filter(Prefix=self._encode_name(name)))
```

