Indeed, this is a limitation: C-style arrays are treated like pointers; there is no way to deduce the length of a returned C-style array, and so no way to automatically bind it.  If you need to work with them, you'll have to use wrapper functions that know the size, such as:

```C++
// Returns c-style int[5]:
m.def("func_a", []() { int *ret = func_a(); return std::vector<int>(ret, ret + 5); });
// Takes c-style int[5]:
m.def("func_b", [](std::array<int, 5> a) { return func_b(a.data()); });
```

