@jni yes, imageio assumes that an image file contains 1 of more images, making index `0` the default. Formats that support just one image will typically raise an error if the index is nonzero. Using `imread()` on a multi-page image file will yield the first image.

We could consider defaulting to `None`, if that helps in this case. But we'd have to adjust the other formats accordingly.

Also worth noting that a Format can provide more methods to extend the API of the reader/writer. Though that only applies to the use of `reader = imageio.get_reader(...)`, not to the simpler `imread` and `mimread()`.

